As of Monday, 1,587 people had lost their lives to  Covid-19 in the metro, the Nelson Mandela Bay municipality said. According to statistics issued by the metro,   561 new cases were recorded on Monday, with 4,602 active cases  and a total of  33,230 recoveries. In a statement issued on Tuesday, the municipality  encouraged Bay residents to make use of mobile testing stations situated in their areas. Hotspot areas around Nelson Mandela Bay were identified  as Motherwell or Ikamvelihle, Soweto-on-Sea, Chatty, Walmer, New Brighton, KwaNobuhle and Cleary Park. The municipality continued to call for residents to practice  safety measures including sanitising, washing hands,  social distancing, avoiding social gatherings and wearing  masks. HeraldLIVE